ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
follows CB's Rules for [i]Beach[/i].
Further prone Troopers with the [i]Wounds[/i] attribute totally inside the Water get the MOD for [i]Partial Cover [/i](also against Templates) and become immune to the effects of [i]Fire[/i] Special Ammunition.
As a drawback the [i]Electric Pulse[/i] automatically hits any kind of Trooper inside the Water on 13 in CC.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
follows CB's Rules for [i]Woods[/i].
The undergrowth patches mark the terrain's area on the table level.
Only the trees, and the space between them, account for the Terrain's height / volume extension.
LOF is blocked by the treetops.

ContainedObjects.Name: Notecard
ContainedObjects.Description:
Only Troops in [b]Silhouette contact[/b] with a window can draw LOF through [u]this[/u] window and to any Troop also in Silhouette contact with a window if the LOF isn't blocked by other elements/windows. Templates are not affected by these LOF restrictions.

Doors can be opened/closed with a short movement skill and are considered open/closed after this short movement order.

ContainedObjects.Description: Technically you could stay here and check out the booze... but since you're most likely a professional operative you won't get distracted by this.

ContainedObjects.Name: Custom_Model
ContainedObjects.Description:
It might look like a museum piece but its simple and robust design makes it easy to build on any planet (even for PanO Engineers). With a maximum payload of one TAG and a full fireteam crashing any beach party will be a breeze.
Retrofitted with aquatic camouflage pattern they don't even see you coming!
